====== sample 1 ======
Q: Define
\[p = \sum_{k = 1}^\infty \frac{1}{k^2} \quad \text{and} \quad q = \sum_{k = 1}^\infty \frac{1}{k^3}.\]Find a way
[block-cond] 524 tok in 27.91s | 18.8 tok/s | acc 9.48/15 | 50 iters
  [ALIGN BUG] iter start=409 pos+1: posterior=400 != oracle=8356  acc=0
[block-cfg] 522 tok in 25.58s | 20.4 tok/s | acc 7.56/15 | 61 iters
A: We are given:

$$
p = \sum_{k = 1}^\infty \frac{1}{k^2}, \quad q = \sum_{k = 1}^\infty \frac{1}{k^3}
$$

and we are to express the double sum:

$$
\sum_{j = 1}^\infty \sum_{k = 1}^\infty \frac{1}{(j + k)^3}
$$

in terms of $ p $ and $ q $.

