====== sample 2 ======
Q: If $f(x) = \frac{3x-2}{x-2}$, what is the value of $f(-2) +f(-1)+f(0)$? Express your answer as a common fraction.
[block-cond] 367 tok in 13.27s | 27.7 tok/s | acc 12.11/15 | 28 iters
[block-cfg] 367 tok in 13.69s | 26.8 tok/s | acc 12.11/15 | 28 iters
A: We are given the function:

$$
f(x) = \frac{3x - 2}{x - 2}
$$

We are asked to find:

$$
f(-2) + f(-1) + f(0)
$$

---

### Step 1: Evaluate $ f(-2) $

$$
f(-2) = \frac{3(-2) - 2}{-2 - 2} = \frac{-6 - 2}{-4} = \frac{-8}{-4} = 2
$$

---

### Step 2: Evaluate $ f(-1) $

$$
f(-1) = \frac{3(-1) - 2}{-1 -
