====== sample 3 ======
Q: How many positive whole-number divisors does 196 have?
[block-cond] 333 tok in 17.25s | 19.3 tok/s | acc 8.79/15 | 34 iters
[block-cfg] 333 tok in 20.92s | 15.9 tok/s | acc 7.12/15 | 41 iters
A: To find how many **positive whole-number divisors** the number **196** has, we follow these steps:

---

### **Step 1: Prime Factorization of 196**

We start by factoring 196 into its prime factors.

$$
196 \div 2 = 98 \\
98 \div 2 = 49 \\
49 \div 7 = 7 \\
7 \div 7 = 1
$$

So, the prime factorizatio
