A: To determine which student has the **greatest average speed**, we need to calculate the **average speed** for each student using the formula:

$$
\text{Average Speed} = \frac{\text{Distance}}{\text{Time}}
$$

From the graph:

- The **x-axis** represents **time** (in some unit, say minutes or seconds
